<p>We would like our robot to follow a trajectory. We used 4 <span class="abbreviation">CIM<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Chiaphua Industrial Motor"></template></span> motors for drivetrain. Two talons for front motors, and two Victors for back motor. Victors follow talons. And our encoders are connected to talons.</p>
<p>When we test our odometry, it works fine. We can see all the movements correctly in the Glass.</p>
<p>Our code is something like below.</p>
<p>When we start the robot, it goes fast for around 0.5 second and slow down suddenly. It reaches the last point correctly but it moves like walk stop and walk stop as you can see the figure… We couldn’t solve why it happens. Does any one has an idea?</p>
